    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>Favored by investigators, judges, and anyone forced to interact with those they don’t trust, a skeptic’s serum is a fizzy technicolor fluid with a sour taste. A skeptic’s serum greatly enhances your senses and amplifies feelings of wariness and suspicion. For 1 hour after you drink this serum, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Sense Motive checks and to saving throws against illusion spells. Once during the duration, if you would fail a saving throw against an illusion spell, you can immediately reroll the saving throw. You must keep the results of the reroll and you can’t reroll this saving throw a second time.</p>"
